palivizumab produces an undiscounted incremental cost-effectiveness ratio (ICER) 
of euro6,142 per quality-adjusted life-year (QALY), and a discounted ICER of 
euro12,814/QALY.
CONCLUSION: Palivizumab provides a cost-effective method of prophylaxis against 
severe RSV disease requiring hospitalisation among preterm infants in Spain.

